    "content": "Cookies Consent Effective date: March 18, 2026 This page explains how Gabriel Services uses cookies and similar technologies on this website, and how you can manage your consent preferences. 1. What cookies are Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website. They help websites function, remember preferences, measure performance, and support security features. Similar technologies such as local storage, pixels, and scripts may be used for related purposes. 2. How we use cookies 3. Manage your preferences You can use the controls below to save your preferences on this device. Strictly necessary cookies remain active because the website relies on them for essential functionality and security. Strictly necessary — required for the website to operate and cannot be turned off here. Preferences — remembers non-essential website choices. Analytics — helps us understand usage and improve the website. Marketing — supports campaign attribution and third-party promotional features when used. Choose your settings and save your preference. 4. Browser controls Most browsers let you block or delete cookies through their settings. If you disable strictly necessary cookies, parts of the website may stop working correctly. Device-level or browser-level settings may override preferences saved on this page. 5. Third-party technologies Some website features may rely on third-party providers such as security verification, embedded media, or external scheduling/contact tools. Optional analytics technologies are currently disabled by default unless a future consent-based implementation is explicitly enabled. When third-party providers place cookies or similar identifiers, their own privacy notices may also apply. 6. Updates to this page We may update this cookie notice and preference experience to reflect changes in law, technology, or website functionality. The latest version will remain available on this page.",
